description:
Bug 3666: Code Completion Hungry code assist (1GDRYW5) 

 Under certain circumstances, the code assist feature in the UI eats too much code. This can be observed when working with the enclosed class.

 As a programmer, when I add a parameter to the 'baz' call in the 'bar' method, the code produced by the code assist is incorrect.

 Steps to Reproduce:

 1. Open the UI and enable the code assist feature.
 2. Edit the 'bar' method in the enclosed class by adding another parameter to the 'baz' call.
 3. Observe that the code assist adds the parameter in the wrong place, causing a compilation error.

 Expected Behavior:

 The code assist should produce the following code: 

 baz(x.foo().foo()) 

 With this correction, the resulting class should be as follows:

public class X {
	void bar(X x) {
		baz(x.foo().foo());
	}
	int foo() {
		return 5;
	}
	void baz(int i, int j) {
	}
}
